main event: Report of unidentified aircraft sounds over Cartwright, Labrador on March 13, 1951, with no visual observation.
interesting points: The report consists solely of sound, with no visual confirmation of an object., Negative report classified as unknown aircraft by the BEEC., Sonic disturbances were typical of transient aircraft in the area., No contact was successfully established with the area regarding the sighting., The aircraft was reported by Carnage ATC and other aviation entities.
sighted object: no object sighted, only sound reported
